/30/gov-brown-signs-law-ending-personal-religious-exemptions-to-school-vaccine-requirements/\">recent legislation in California</a> that removed the personal-belief exemption from public health vaccination programmes. </p> <p>Carrey’s tweet was posted on Instagram by Echols’ aunt Elizabeth Welch. Carrey wrote: “A trillion dollars buys a lot of expert opinions. Will it buy you? TOXIN FREE VACCINES, A REASONABLE REQUEST!” accompanied by a picture of Echols. Welch accused Carrey of using the post to “mock” him and and his family, and that vaccinations played no part in his condition.</p> <p>Karen Echols followed up with a direct appeal to Carrey asking him to remove the picture. The tweet was deleted and Carrey apologised in a subsequent message.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-embed\" data-alt=\"Karen Echols tweet\">  <iframe class=\"fenced\" srcdoc=\"&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&quot;twitter-tweet&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p lang=&quot;en&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JimCarrey&quot;&gt;@JimCarrey&lt;/a&gt; Please remove this photo of my son. You do not have permission to use his image.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Karen Echols (@karen_echols) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/karen_echols/status/616411579773419520&quot;&gt;July 2, 2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;script async src=&quot;//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\"></iframe> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-embed\" data-alt=\"Jim Carrey tweet\">  <iframe class=\"fenced\" srcdoc=\"&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&quot;twitter-tweet&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p lang=&quot;en&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;I&amp;#39;d like to apologize to the Echols family and others for posting a pic of their kids w/o permission.I didn&amp;#39;t mean to cause them distress.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Jim Carrey (@JimCarrey) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JimCarrey/status/616775401197539328&quot;&gt;July 3, 2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;script async src=&quot;//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\"></iframe> </figure>  <p>The supposed link between autism and the MMR vaccine was comprehensively disproved after a <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/apr/21/no-link-between-mmr-and-autism-major-study-concludes\">major study published in the Journal of the American Medical Association</a>. The researcher who put forward the original suggestion in 1998, Andrew Wakefield, was <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/society/2010/may/24/mmr-doctor-andrew-wakefield-struck-off\">struck off the the GMC medical register in 2010 for “serious professional misconduct”.</a></p>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"Actor in anti-vaccine protest on Twitter comes under fire after attaching picture, but apologises after contact from boy’s family","headline":"Jim Carrey apologises after tweeting child's picture without permission","byline":"Andrew Pulver","commentable":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4adjq","wordcount":"192","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/7/6/1436197317967/2457832c-20d1-4ef6-94fa-70911992bece-140x84.jpeg","commentCloseDate":"2015-07-10T07:33:36Z","standfirst":"<p>Actor in anti-vaccine protest on Twitter comes under fire after attaching picture, but apologises after contact from boy’s family</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/jul/07/jim-carrey-apologises-tweet-child-photo-without-permssion-autism-vaccine","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/jul/07/jim-carrey-apologises-tweet-child-photo-without-permssion-autism-vaccine","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/jimcarrey","webTitle":"Jim Carrey","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/jimcarrey","api