nt element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2015/jun/18/five-things-we-know-about-paul-feigs-ghostbusters\">Ghostbusters: five things we know as Paul Feig's reboot starts shooting</a> </p> </aside>  <p>The three join the film’s four main supernatural-crime fighters – Kristen Wiig, Melissa McCarthy, Leslie Jones and Kate McKinnon – and Chris Hemsworth, who plays the ladies’ hunky receptionist in the revamp.<br /></p> <p>Garcia has been cast as the mayor of New York City. Williams, of Boardwalk Empire and The Wire fame, joins the project, which is currently shooting in Boston, as a character named Hawkins. Strong, who is currently on a hiatus from Saturday Night Live, will play an unconfirmed character. </p> <p>Other new cast members include Veep star Matt Walsh and Pat Kiernan, the longtime morning anchor of New York City’s NY1, who will riff on his day job in the film as a news anchor.</p>","productionOffice":"US","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"Saturday Night Live alum Cecily Strong has also joined the high-profile cast of Paul Feig’s anticipated comedy blockbuster","headline":"Ghostbusters reboot casts Andy Garcia and Michael K Williams","byline":"Nigel M Smith","commentable":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4adqh","wordcount":"152","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/7/6/1436217628818/7ae4a0cd-8c47-4fab-a993-b03be2945d93-140x84.jpeg","commentCloseDate":"2015-07-09T17:45:00-04:00","standfirst":"<p>Saturday Night Live alum Cecily Strong has also joined the high-profile cast of Paul Feig’s anticipated comedy blockbuster</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/jul/06/ghostbusters-reboot-andy-garcia-michael-k-williams-cecily-strong","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/jul/06/ghostbusters-reboot-andy-garcia-michael-k-williams-cecily-strong","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/ghostbusters","webTitle":"Ghostbuster