ks box office records","references":[],"webPublicationDate":"2015-07-06T14:38:10Z","fields":{"liveBloggingNow":"false","body":"<p>A remarkable initial box office performance has given a substantial awards push to Asif Kapadia’s documentary about the late singer Amy Winehouse.</p> <p>Amy, which has earned <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/jul/02/amy-winehouse-review-documentary\">five-star reviews</a> and picked up strong word-of-mouth since premiering at Cannes in May, recorded the biggest ever opening weekend for a British documentary in the UK, and the second biggest (discounting concert films) of all time. </p>       <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/video/2015/jul/03/amy-magic-mike-terminator-genisys-magician-reviews-guardian\"            data-short-url=\"http://gu.com/p/4abpp\"                    data-show-ads=\"true\"            data-video-id=\"2331313\"            data-video-name=\"The Guardian film show live: Amy, Terminator Genisys, Magic Mike XXL and Orson Welles – video reviews\"            data-video-provider=\"guardian.co.uk\"            data-video-poster=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2015/7/3/1435920840528/KP_339196_crop_640x360.jpg\"> <video data-media-id=\"gu-video-457398607\" class=\"gu-video\" controls=\"controls\" poster=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2015/7/3/1435920837186/KP_339196_crop_1200x720.jpg\"> <source src=\"http://cdn.theguardian.tv/mainwebsite/2015/07/03/150702TGFSmain_1_desk.mp4\"></source><source src=\"http://cdn.theguardian.tv/3gp/small/2015/07/03/150702TGFSmain_1_small.3gp\"></source><source src=\"http://cdn.theguardian.tv/3gp/large/2015/07/03/150702TGFSmain_1_large.3gp\"></source><source src=\"http://cdn.theguardian.tv/HLS/2015/07/03/150702TGFSmain_1.m3u8\"></source><source src=\"http://cdn.theguardian.tv/webM/2015/07/03/150702TGFSmain_1_synd_768k_vp8.webm\"></source> </video> <figcaption>Watch a review of the film and an interview with Kapadia</figcaption> </figure>  <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/jun/27/asif-kapadia-amy-winehouse-doc\">Asif Kapadia on Amy: ‘The drinking, the bulimia, the drugs – nobody stopped it’</a> </p> </aside>  <p>Only Michael Moore’s 2004 polemic, Fahrenheit 9/11, surpassed it; that film went on to take $12m in the UK, a figure Amy is now chasing. The film opened over a remarkably sunny UK weekend in 133 cinemas; from 10 July, that will expand to over 200 – a pre-planned expansion rollout unusual in the UK. </p> <p>Both the success and the strategy are mimicked in the US, where Amy opened with $222,015 across six sites, with a location average of $37,002 – $10,000 more than Fahrenheit 9/11 managed on its first weekend and even beating March of the Penguins’s $34,373 back in 2005. The film will expand nationwide in the US on 10 July. </p>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"In the UK, Asif Kapadia’s study of the late singer has charted the highest ever box office for a homegrown non-fiction film, and scored a $37,002 site average in the US","headline":"Amy Winehouse documentary breaks box office records","byline":"Catherine Shoard","commentable":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4adhq","wordcount":"201","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/7/6/1436192077731/b605ab1e-5d35-4ffc-9d26-8802c36a3c89-140x84.jpeg","commentCloseDate":"2015-07-13T15:45:00+01:00","standfirst":"<p>In the UK, Asif Kapadia’s study of the late singer has charted the highest ever box office for a homegrown non-fiction film, and scored a $37,002 site average in the US</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/jul/06/amy-winehouse-documentary-breaks-records-box-office","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/jul/06/amy-winehouse-documentary-breaks-records-box-office","section