 of Boys Don’t Cry and Million Dollar Baby <a href=\"http://live.huffingtonpost.com/r/segment/hilary-swank-support-the-troops-uso-duracell-interview-/558315f52b8c2af7e700036d\">told Huffpost Live</a> she was happy to take time out to <a href=\"http://www.pikore.com/m/1012508546575087053_1216097540\">spend time with Stephen Swank</a>, a former chief master sergeant in the Oregon Air National Guard who recently underwent a lung transplant.</p> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/apr/10/hilary-swank-a-long-way-to-go-before-transphobia-wiped-out-lgbt\">Hilary Swank: 'A long way to go before transphobia wiped out'</a> </p> </aside>  <p>“My dad is living with me,” said Swank. “I’m his sole caretaker right now.”</p> <p>She added: “It’s a certain amount of time, but in a lifespan it’s a blink of an eye. There’s been job opportunities I’ve passed on, and things that I said ‘I can’t’, but really what we’re here for is our family.</p> <p>“There is nothing I want to do more other than being with my dad in this time of need. And if it wasn’t me taking care of him, I think I would always look back and regret that opportunity to be able to take care of him and help him through this extraordinary time.”</p> <p>Swank was being interviewed to promote a new campaign highlighting the difficulties the families of American service people face when their loved ones are away in war zones. She said spending time with her father helped to make up for the times the pair spent apart during her youth.</p> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/nov/18/hilary-swank-male-actors-earn-10-times-more-than-female\">Hilary Swank: male actors earn 10 times more than female</a> </p> </aside>  <p>“We’re super close,” she said. “The bond that we’ve made in this time, might make up for some of that time we didn’t have. We didn’t have that one-on-one time together. It’s actually kind of healing.”</p> <p>Swank is next due to star in the Alejandro González Iñárritu television series The One Percent, opposite Ed Helms. She also has the 2016 animated film Spark on her slate, and is <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/apr/28/hilary-swank-and-tom-wilkinson-to-star-in-holocaust-denier-drama\">due to headline a new drama about Holocaust denier David Irving</a>, titled Denial, opposite Tom Wilkinson.</p>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"Star of Boys Don’t Cry and Million Dollar Baby says she has ‘passed’ on roles to help look after her father after his lung transplant","headline":"Hilary Swank scaling back acting career to take care of ailing father","byline":"Ben Child","commentable":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4ada2","wordcount":"330","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/7/6/1436177453350/d3a9c6db-ef5e-470a-a072-4357fce946d7-140x84.jpeg","commentCloseDate":"2015-07-13T11:00:00+01:00","standfirst":"<p>Star of Boys Don’t Cry and Million Dollar Baby says she has ‘passed’ on roles to help look after her father after his lung transplant</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/jul/06/hilary-swank-scaling-back-acting-career-to-take-care-of-ailing-father","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/jul/06/hilary-swank-scaling-back-acting-career-to-take-care-of-ailing-father","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/film","webTitle":"Film","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/film","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/film","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"film/hilaryswank","webTitle":"Hilary Swank","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/hilaryswank","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/hilaryswank","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Cul